---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import CallButton from '../../components/CallButton.astro';

const siteUrl = 'https://windshieldreplacementlubbock.com';
const postUrl = `${siteUrl}/blog/lubbock-hail-season-windshield-damage/`;
---

<Layout
  title="Lubbock Hail Season: What to Do When Your Windshield Gets Hit"
  description="After a Lubbock hailstorm damages your windshield, here's exactly what to do — documenting damage, filing an insurance claim, and getting on the schedule before shops fill up."
  canonical={postUrl}
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Lubbock Hail Season: What to Do When Your Windshield Gets Hit",
    "description": "A step-by-step guide for Lubbock drivers dealing with hail windshield damage — documenting damage, filing an insurance claim, understanding repair vs. replacement, and why timing matters.",
    "url": postUrl,
    "datePublished": "2025-06-13",
    "dateModified": "2025-06-13",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Lubbock Windshield Replacement",
      "url": siteUrl
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Lubbock Windshield Replacement",
      "url": siteUrl
    },
    "mainEntityOfPage": {
      "@type": "WebPage",
      "@id": postUrl
    }
  })} />
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does insurance cover hail damage to my windshield in Texas?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, if you have comprehensive coverage. Hail is a comprehensive claim — not collision. Comprehensive pays for damage from weather events, falling objects, and road hazards. Filing a hail claim in Texas does not raise your rates, as it is a not-at-fault event."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Will my windshield need to be replaced after hail, or can it be repaired?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "It depends on the size and number of impacts. Light hail may create individual chips that are individually repairable. Moderate to heavy hail typically creates multiple impact points scattered across the glass, which almost always requires full replacement. One comprehensive claim covers all storm damage with one deductible."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When is hail season in Lubbock, TX?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Lubbock's primary hail season runs from March through June, with April and May being the most active months. Lubbock sits in the southern Plains storm track and sees some of the most active hail seasons in the country. Wind-driven hail in West Texas tends to create more severe glass damage than vertical hail."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I wait a week before getting my hail-damaged windshield replaced?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You can, but it creates two problems: auto glass shops fill up fast after a major storm, so waiting means a longer queue. And leaving cracked glass in West Texas heat causes existing cracks to run further as the glass expands in the sun. Get on the schedule quickly even if your appointment is still a few days out."
        }
      }
    ]
  })} />
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": `${siteUrl}/` },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Blog", "item": `${siteUrl}/blog/` },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Lubbock Hail Season: What to Do When Your Windshield Gets Hit", "item": postUrl }
    ]
  })} />

  <Header />

  <section style="background-color: #1e3a8a;" class="text-white py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-blue-300 text-sm font-medium mb-3">
        <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/`} class="hover:text-white transition-colors">&#8592; Blog</a>
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-3">Lubbock Hail Season: What to Do When Your Windshield Gets Hit</h1>
      <p class="text-blue-200 text-lg max-w-2xl">A step-by-step guide for the hours right after a storm — documenting damage, filing your claim, and getting on the schedule before every shop fills up.</p>
      <p class="text-blue-300 text-sm mt-4">Updated June 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <div class="mb-10 p-5 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl">
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-3">Dealing with hail damage right now? Call us and we'll get you on the schedule — and handle the insurance claim for you if you'd rather not.</p>
      <CallButton label="Call (806) 450-8900 — Get on the Schedule" size="md" />
    </div>

    <section class="mb-10 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You walk outside after a spring storm and the damage is already obvious. Dents in the hood, pits in the roof, and your windshield looking like someone threw a handful of rocks at it. This is what to do in the next few hours.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        The steps matter here. The sequence matters more. Shops fill up fast after a major Lubbock storm, and leaving cracked glass sitting in West Texas heat makes things worse every day you wait.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Why Lubbock's Hail Season Is Genuinely Different</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Lubbock sits at the southern end of the Plains storm track — the system that pulls Gulf moisture north through West Texas every spring. March through June is prime season, with April and May being the most active months. Most years, at least one or two significant hail events roll through Lubbock. Some years it's worse.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        What makes West Texas hail particularly hard on glass isn't just the size of the stones. It's the wind. A horizontal hailstorm driven by 40-mph plains winds hits glass at a more severe angle than vertical hail. That's why you'll sometimes see windshield damage on the side glass as well as the top of a vehicle after a bad event. If you've lived here more than a year, you've probably already been through at least one of these.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-5" style="color: #1e3a8a;">The Steps — In Order</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-5 py-3 flex items-center gap-3" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">1</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">Check the Damage Before You Drive</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Before you start the car, actually look at the windshield.</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">&#10003;</span> Multiple impact pits without cracks running from them — structurally intact, driveable</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold">!</span> Cracks running from impact points, especially toward the edge — drive as little as possible</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-bold">&#215;</span> Glass shattered or displaced — don't drive it; call us at (806) 450-8900</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">
              Take photos before you touch anything. Insurance adjusters want to see the damage in its original state, and you want documentation before any changes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-5 py-3 flex items-center gap-3" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">2</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">Document Everything — Windshield and the Rest</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Hail doesn't just hit your windshield. Walk the whole car before you do anything else.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Hood dents, roof damage, rear glass, side mirrors — document all of it. Here's why this matters: all damage from a single storm event falls under one comprehensive claim with <strong>one deductible</strong>. If you file the windshield separately and notice the hood damage later, you might end up with two claims. Document everything at once, file one claim, cover it all with one deductible.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Take close-ups of each impact and wider shots showing the overall damage pattern.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-5 py-3 flex items-center gap-3" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">3</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">File Your Insurance Claim — Hail = Comprehensive</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Hail damage is a comprehensive claim — not collision. Comprehensive covers weather events, road debris, falling objects. If you have it, you're covered. For how Texas insurance handles these claims in detail, see our full guide: <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/does-insurance-cover-windshield-replacement-texas/`} style="color: #1e3a8a;" class="font-medium hover:underline">Does Insurance Cover Windshield Replacement in Texas?</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Filing is straightforward: call the claims number on your insurance card or use your insurer's app, tell them you have hail damage from the storm date, and get a claim number.
            </p>
            <div class="p-3 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong>One important note:</strong> filing a hail claim does not raise your rates in Texas. Hail is a not-at-fault event — you didn't cause the storm.
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">Or call us first at <a href="tel:+18064508900" style="color: #1e3a8a;" class="font-medium hover:underline">(806) 450-8900</a>. We can start the claim on your behalf if you'd rather not deal with the insurer directly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-5 py-3 flex items-center gap-3" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">4</span>
            <span class="text-white font-semibold">Get on the Schedule — Don't Wait</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              After a significant hail event hits Lubbock, every auto glass shop in town fills up. It's not unusual to see booking queues stretch 3–5 days after a major storm. Get in the queue early.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              And there's a second reason not to wait: leaving hail-damaged glass parked in direct West Texas sun accelerates cracking. Hail impacts create stress fractures. Summer heat causes glass to expand. Those two things together mean existing damage runs faster than usual. A windshield that looks bad but intact on Monday can look considerably worse by Thursday.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-sm">
              If you can park the vehicle in a garage or shaded area while you wait for your appointment, do it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Hail Damage: Repair or Replacement?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Most of the time after a significant Lubbock storm, windshield replacement is the answer. Here's how to think about it:
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-5">
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 font-bold text-green-700 text-sm w-32">Light hail<br/><span class="font-normal text-green-600">pea-sized</span></div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">May create individual chips that can be repaired separately. Call and describe the damage — if you have fewer than 3–4 isolated chips with no long cracks, repair might be possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 font-bold text-yellow-700 text-sm w-32">Moderate hail<br/><span class="font-normal text-yellow-600">marble–quarter</span></div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Multiple impact points scattered across the glass. Repair works on isolated chips, not a field of damage. This is almost always replacement territory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 font-bold text-red-700 text-sm w-32">Heavy hail<br/><span class="font-normal text-red-600">golf ball+</span></div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Replacement. No question about it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Not sure which category you're in? Our <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/chip-vs-crack-windshield-repair-lubbock/`} style="color: #1e3a8a;" class="font-medium hover:underline">chip vs. crack guide</a> covers the repair decision rules in detail, or call and describe what you see.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1e3a8a;">What About the Rest of Your Car?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If the hail hit your windshield, it almost certainly hit your hood and roof too. Body panel damage and glass damage are handled by different shops, but both fall under that single comprehensive claim.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Coordinate your timing so you're not juggling two separate repair appointments without your vehicle for days at a time. Schedule the windshield first since you need the car to be safely driveable — body shop work can usually wait a few extra days without causing additional problems.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Multiple Vehicles in the Same Storm</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Lubbock families often have two or three vehicles parked outside. A hailstorm hits them all at once. Each vehicle is its own separate insurance claim with its own deductible — that's unavoidable. But the process is the same for each.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Give us the information for all your vehicles when you call. We can often schedule back-to-back appointments and knock out multiple vehicles on the same day or two, so you're not without a second or third car for extended periods.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Vehicles with ADAS Safety Cameras</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If your vehicle has a front-facing camera for lane-keep assist, automatic emergency braking, or adaptive cruise control — which includes most F-150s, Silverados, RAMs, and newer Corollas and Camrys — the camera needs to be recalibrated after windshield replacement.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Most comprehensive insurance policies cover recalibration as part of the glass claim. It's a required step, not an optional add-on. A shop that skips recalibration to speed up the job is leaving your safety systems miscalibrated — which means they may not work correctly when you actually need them.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Tell us your vehicle year, make, and model when you call. We'll confirm whether recalibration applies and how it gets handled with your insurer.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">What It Costs — and What Insurance Pays</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you have comprehensive coverage, hail windshield damage is covered. You pay your deductible; insurance covers the rest. Many Texas policies also have a separate, lower glass deductible — worth checking before you assume you'll pay your full deductible.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        For a full breakdown of windshield replacement costs by vehicle in the Lubbock area, see our <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/windshield-replacement-cost-lubbock-tx/`} style="color: #1e3a8a;" class="font-medium hover:underline">windshield replacement cost guide</a>. And for the full picture on how Texas insurance handles glass claims, see <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/does-insurance-cover-windshield-replacement-texas/`} style="color: #1e3a8a;" class="font-medium hover:underline">Does Insurance Cover Windshield Replacement in Texas?</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Will my rates go up after a hail claim?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">No, typically not. Hail is a comprehensive claim in Texas and is classified as not-at-fault. Your rates should not increase for a hail event claim. If you've filed several comprehensive claims in a short period, confirm with your agent — but a standard hail claim almost never moves your rate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I wait a week before calling?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Technically yes, but two things work against you: shops fill up fast after storms, and West Texas heat causes existing cracks to run. Get on the schedule quickly even if your appointment is a few days out. At least you're in the queue before everyone else calls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does hail damage require replacement, or can chips from hail be repaired?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Depends entirely on the severity of the hail. Light hail with a few isolated impacts may be repairable chip by chip. Moderate to heavy hail with impacts scattered across the glass is almost always a replacement. Call us and describe what you see — we'll tell you honestly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pb-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What if the storm hit overnight and I'm not sure when it happened?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">The date and time of the storm is established by weather records, not your personal account. Your insurer will know about any significant storm event that hit Lubbock. Just file the claim with the approximate date and describe when you discovered the damage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Related Articles</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/does-insurance-cover-windshield-replacement-texas/`} class="block p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1 font-medium">Insurance</p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm leading-snug">Does Insurance Cover Windshield Replacement in Texas?</p>
        </a>
        <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/chip-vs-crack-windshield-repair-lubbock/`} class="block p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1 font-medium">Repair Guide</p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm leading-snug">Chip vs. Crack: Can Your Windshield Be Repaired?</p>
        </a>
        <a href={`${siteUrl}/blog/windshield-replacement-cost-lubbock-tx/`} class="block p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1 font-medium">Pricing &amp; Cost</p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm leading-snug">How Much Does Windshield Replacement Cost in Lubbock, TX?</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="text-center py-10 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Storm Hit? Call and Get on the Schedule.</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-5 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        After a Lubbock hailstorm, every day you wait means more time for cracks to run in the Texas heat — and a longer queue at every shop in town. Call us at (806) 450-8900 and we'll handle the insurance claim and get you scheduled fast.
      </p>
      <CallButton label="Call (806) 450-8900 — Same-Day Available" size="lg" center={true} />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Mobile service across all of Lubbock, TX</p>
    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
